lead_paragraph: Because of an editing error, an article last Monday in the special U.S. Open Preview section about the crowded competition for the No. 1 ranking in women’s tennis misidentified one of the three Russian women to win singles medals at the Beijing Olympics. In addition to Elena Dementieva and Dinara Safina, Vera Zvonareva claimed a medal. Their countrywoman Svetlana Kuznetsova did not.
